                <div class="panel panel-body" id="berlin-cult-tips-body">
                    <ol class="list-items" id="cultural-tip-items">
                        <h4>
                            <li>
                                Most Germans speak English so Germany is effectively one of the worst places to practice your spoken German.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Waiters & Waitresses tend to leave patrons alone while eating, thus placing one's silverware facing inward on one's plate
                                at a 1 or 2 O'Clock position denotes to a server that one is finished with their meal.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Germans commonly take their shoes off while in someone else's home or their own.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                In Germany and several other countries in Europe public restrooms are somewhat of a rarity. Businesses will commonly require
                                you to purchase something in order to use the restrooms, but in most cases one must pay anywhere
                                from €,20-€2,00. A word to the wise, do your business before leaving home.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                In Germany, and most of Europe for that fact, it is rude or unsettling to not say "hello" or "goodbye."
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Using the word "Fräulein" is less common in modern times as it denotes a female that is unmarried, "Frau" is the standard
                                for the majority of women today.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                The word for "blue" in German is "blau," which also means "drunk."
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                While technically illegal, drinking in public is "tolerated" if one does not get out of control, and in some cities seen
                                as "cool" just to be seen carrying a bottle of beer.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Privacy is a big issue in Germany, understand it and respect it.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                DO NOT DO ANYTHING RELATED TO NAZIS...SALUTING, TAGGING, ETC...IT IS ILLEGAL IN GERMANY!
                            </li>
                        </h4>
                    </ol>
