                        <li>
                            "Hallo" (hallow) - "Hello", one of the most common words used to greet someone (informal).
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            "Tschüß" (choo-ss) - "Goodbye", one of the most frequently used words for goodbye (informal).
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            "Bitte" (Bit-uh) - Has several meanings, the most common being "Please", "You're Welcome", & "Pardon?".
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            "Danke" (Donk-uh) - "Thanks", can be combined with "schön" (shun) to say "Thank you very much".
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Wo (voh) - "Where" + ist = "Where is".
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            "Rechnung" (resh-nuhng) - "Check", useful when asking for the check at a restaurant.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            "Entschuldigung" (ent-shul-dee-guhng) - "Pardon" or "Excuse Me" (This is the short version).
